The paper deals with a problem related to computing medians in subarrays defined by intervals in an unsorted array. This problem is a classic one in data structures and algorithms, and is typically studied in the context of computational geometry and discrete mathematics. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). Additionally, the paper mentions that the algorithm has natural generalizations to higher dimensional problems, which suggests that it may be relevant to computational geometry (cs.CG) and possibly also to information theory (cs.IT) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper involves some analysis of the time and space complexity of the algorithm, which is a common theme in discrete mathematics (cs.DM).
